Throw this command:
sh /usr/share/wallpaper_manager/w_m/w_m-speech-reco.sh
and you can add to a shortcut keyboard. Or a panel roper:
 /usr/share/wallpaper_manager/w_m/app-panel/w_m-speech-reco.sh-1.desktop
Title:
wallpaper audio recognition
And executable path:
/usr/share/wallpaper_manager/w_m/w_m-speech-reco.sh
Path to the icon audio recognition:
/usr/share/wallpaper_manager/w_m/iconos/w_m-audio-reco.png

You can modify the commands in the file: /usr/share/wallpaper_manager/w_m/actions/w_m-speech-reco-cmd-en
Microphone settings, you can make with the string: michrophone_port=1, this set the port activation, this you should modify to your chosen microphone port, Audio in, select: Microphone, Internal Mic not.
Works with goolge Speech recognition
